Q3. Business Logic

Business logic refers to the rules and decisions that define how a web application should behave according to real-world needs of the business or system.

It decides:

what actions are allowed

what calculations must be applied

what data should be stored or rejected

what conditions must be satisfied

It sits between the frontend and database and is usually implemented in the backend.

Real-world examples

E-commerce website

If cart value > ₹1000 → give free shipping

Prevent checkout if product is out of stock

Banking application

Block transfer if balance is insufficient

Apply interest differently for savings vs current accounts

Online learning platform

Issue certificate only if user completes all modules

Lock next chapter until previous quiz is passed
